{
  "id": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000005",
  "name": "Getting Started",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1738368000000,
  "modified": 1775756665823,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A quick orientation for new users. Everything you need to start using "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c3f4c6ad-e827-4999-bf22-724873a5aade"
          },
          {
            "s": "Hobson"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " — the rest you can discover from within the system itself."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Everything Is an Item"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "In Hobson, there are no files, folders, or apps — just "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "items"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Notes, tasks, code, views, types, this documentation, even the entire UI — all items. Every item has a type, a set of content fields, and can link to other items. This uniformity means you only need to learn one set of interactions."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Multiple Views"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "An item can be viewed in different ways, depending on its type. You are probably reading this note in \"readonly view\" (right-click > View As... to see what view is currently being used, and what alternatives are available)."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Spatial Canvas"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "When you open Hobson, you are probably looking at a "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "4bbe108c-9db9-430d-a65d-7b5a00831bbb"
          },
          {
            "s": "workspace"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " rendered as a "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "ef793c27-2d4b-4c99-b05a-2769db5bc5a9"
          },
          {
            "s": "spatial canvas"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " — a freeform canvas where items appear as draggable, resizable windows. Think of it as an infinite desk where you arrange your stuff. The workspace you are currently in is probably \"New Users\" (check the name in the browser tab), which has been set up with useful information for first-time users. The "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "Ctrl+K"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " keyboard shortcut (see below) will show \"starred items\" that include other workspaces."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The reason for saying that you are \"probably\" in \"New Users\" is that any item can be attached to any other item, so it is perfectly possibly to come across the \"Getting Started\" item in another context."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Key shortcuts"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "Ctrl+Shift+?"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " show the shortcut help modal, which describes all the shortcuts, as shown below (by the way, that is generated by the actual help modal code, it is not a screenshot. Click the source name to jump to the code)."
        }
      ],
      [
        "do",
        [
          "transclusion-chrome",
          [
            "call-export",
            "@f1111111-0006-0000-0000-000000000000",
            {
              "s": "buildHelpPanel"
            },
            "api"
          ],
          ":source",
          "@f1111111-0006-0000-0000-000000000000",
          ":symbol",
          {
            "s": "buildHelpPanel"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Right-Click Everything"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "context menu"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " is your primary tool. Right-click on any item (remember, everything is an item) — to see actions: edit, delete, change view, inspect, and more"
        }
      ],
      [
        "do",
        [
          "transclusion-chrome",
          [
            "call-export",
            "@2cc0a1c5-5c09-49bd-834a-eaa2d0183b6c",
            {
              "s": "buildItemMenu"
            },
            "api",
            {
              "m": [
                [
                  ":itemId",
                  "@c0c0c0c0-0054-0000-0000-000000000000"
                ]
              ]
            }
          ],
          ":source",
          "@2cc0a1c5-5c09-49bd-834a-eaa2d0183b6c",
          ":symbol",
          {
            "s": "buildItemMenu"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "When in doubt, right-click. The menu is context-sensitive and will show you what's possible. See "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0034-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Context Menu"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " for details."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Creating Items"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Right-click on the canvas background and choose "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Add Item"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " > "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "New Item"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Pick a type (note, task, or any custom type) and a new item appears on the canvas (it has become part of the canvas's "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0005-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Attachments"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "). "
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Note that you are not restricted to just attaching items to the canvas. The same behaviour applies to any items, but depending on what "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000004"
          },
          {
            "s": "View"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " is rendering the item, you might not see the item you just attached (though it will always be listed in the Related Items item on the right hand side of this page). In that case you can use the context menu to change the view."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Navigating Into Items"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Items can contain other items via "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0005-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "attachments"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Use an item's context menu to "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "navigate into"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " it, making it the root of your canvas. See "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0003-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Navigation"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Links and Transclusion"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Items can reference each other in two ways:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Links"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — In the doc editor, type "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "@"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " to search and insert item references. In code, write "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "[link text](item://guid)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " to create a clickable link to another item."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Transclusion"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — In the doc editor, type "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "@@"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " to search and insert item content."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Transclusion can also target specific fields or line ranges. See "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0035-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Transclusion"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " for the full syntax."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Tags and Related Items"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Any item can act as a "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0021-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "tag"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Tagging is lightweight classification — add tags via an item's edit view. Tags help you find and filter items without imposing a rigid hierarchy. The "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Related Items"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " item show everything that is somehow connected to the currently selected item."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Search"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Press "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "Ctrl+K"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " to open the "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "item palette"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " — a search over all items by free text, name ("
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "name:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ") or tag ("
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "tag:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "). Start typing to filter, then click on an item to open it as the root item."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "If you want a search facility that adds items to your existing workspace, then add the \"Item Search\" item to the workspace (right-click > Add Child > Existing Item and then query "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "name:\"Item Search\""
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " to find the correct item to add. This item will behave exactly like "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "Ctrl+k"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", except that the default action when clicking a result is to add it to the workspace."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Alternatively, in a workspace the shortcuts "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "Ctrl+Shift+N"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "Ctrl+Shift+A"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " can be used to attach New/Existing items."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The REPL"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Press "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "Ctrl+\\"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " to toggle the "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0008-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "REPL"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " — an interactive console with full access to the kernel API. You can query items, create them programmatically, test code, or inspect system state. It's entirely optional for day-to-day use, but powerful when you need it."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Safe Mode"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "If something goes wrong (a bad code item, a broken view), add "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "?safe=1"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " to the URL. This boots only the kernel — no user code runs — so you can fix or delete the offending item. See "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0031-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "URL Parameters"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Where to Go From Here"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "If you want examples of what it can do:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "1c00dfe9-cc76-415d-bb27-451a3cfaacd2"
              },
              {
                "s": "Create Nested Instance"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " and "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "210cd1d3-56f3-4cd4-8192-170dcae2707c"
              },
              {
                "s": "Theme Editor"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " are examples of "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0038-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "App Pages"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " - simple apps that can be quickly built by dragging and dropping \"widgets\" on a page."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "ac0ac0ac-0008-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "Symbol Browser"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "- explore the code and jump straight to the implementation"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "349dfca4-1b10-4eb8-85ab-41113b5fcaf6"
              },
              {
                "s": "System Browser"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " - browse all types, tags, views, libraries; find all implementations, jump to items."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "eeee0000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001"
              },
              {
                "s": "element-inspector"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " - see exactly what code generated any visual element on the screen."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "56a2c83c-1fd4-4db7-a3e8-3aa152524721"
              },
              {
                "s": "Test Suite"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " - some automated tests that run within a "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0037-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "Nested Hobson Instance"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "If you want a summary of the implemented features, go to "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0092-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Feature Overview"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Alternatively, open the "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "a63eadd8-ec56-4163-acf2-207aa392069b"
          },
          {
            "s": "feature"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " tag and click on it to see lots of useful related material in the \"Related Items\" on the right."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Some suggestions for a technical overview:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0091-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "System Layers"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — A high level of the kernel/viewport/userland split"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000002"
              },
              {
                "s": "Core Concepts"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — Items, types, code, libraries, views"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000003"
              },
              {
                "s": "Architecture Overview"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — How the system is built"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000001"
              },
              {
                "s": "Philosophy & Inspirations"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — Why Hobson works the way it does"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "a0a0a0a0-d0c0-4000-8000-000000000004"
              },
              {
                "s": "Views & Rendering"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — How items get displayed, and how to build custom views"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "If you want to browse technical concepts, open the "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "bff75873-edb8-412e-81c9-c744e68fe29f"
          },
          {
            "s": "concept"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " tag and click on it to see lots of useful related material in the \"Related Items\" on the right."
        }
      ]
    ],
    "tags": [
      "c3f4c6ad-e827-4999-bf22-724873a5aade",
      "c0c0c0c0-0085-0000-0000-000000000000"
    ]
  },
  "attachments": []
}